rComments: Professor Beaulieu links dozens of youtube links in her brightspace that only explain the base material and the course is asynchronous. Her midterms and exams are open book but are difficult to do well on due to the obscurity of the questions. She provides little review material or constructive feedback so it's hard to know where to improve.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Loved her, interesting lectures and fair assignments and midterms: might be the first time I enjoyed writing a midterm. The case study style was very fun. She writes an encouraging announcement every week and helps us get organized. Very caring and accommodating. The final was pickier with answers, but she did warn us to provide detail, so yah

This class was a rollercoaster for me. The midterms were fair and could be done well easily without attending lectures since they are take home exams. On the other hand the Final exam did not reflect the difficulty of the midterms and was much harder. I spent 8 hours on the exam and got a 60%. The rest of the work is easy and free points.

Idky everyone here is complaining so much, shes a great prof. Our class average was 81 percent. Those who are complaining must have somehow done less then the bare minimum as we were given more then a day to do the final exam and midterms. I didnt really study and got an A+. But dont get me wrong the tests were still pretty tough.

One of my favourite classes I've taken!! She makes the lectures interesting and I even enjoyed the case studies and midterms. A lot of application questions but if you watch the lectures you should be fine. I'm not even in a science degree and I did well. I don't know why she's getting bad ratings I don't have any complaints.

This course was well structured. The exam questions are pretty application based over general knowledge. A lot of comments on here complain about how shes not an easy marker but most will complain that they dont get part Mark's for wrong answers. Most will also not open the textbook once or will read over their notes. Good proff.

A lot of students are leaving bad reviews because of the final. But, I think people just did not study for the final since the second midterm was so easy (you could literally get an A without watching or reading any lecture beforehand). She's a really sweet prof. There is a lottttt of very easy marks (case studies, quizzes, stekch evaluation).

The questions she will ask are not confusing. The issue is that she has no part marks (u will never get a 0.5 for a 1 pointer unless it was something specified from her rubric), and requires you to be VERY SPECIFIC. A question worth 6 marks might actually want 12 different points lol. avoid if possible, very easy to mess up. (Not butthurt)

Lectures are interesting. Grading is awful, midterms were okay but the final was graded harshly. The final exam instructed us to be brief but the prof wanted detailed answers with specific keywords according to her rubric. A question was worth 2 points but apparently needed 4 points with each point awarding you a 0.5 mark. ��

I am not complaining here since I got an A+ for the overall class grade, but the final exam marking scheme is somewhat unfair. She is looking for detailed extended answers and not just 1 sentence or so. I spent 22 hours writing the exam and got an A- on it. I don't feel like the effort I put in this class is awarded by the final exam mark I got.

Sorry but most of y'all are angry because you didn't give detailed answers. She specifically asked for detailed answers for the final and we had 1 day to complete this exam. She's not the worst you just have to listen to her carefully and write everything she says then you'll be good. This is a 3rd year course I don't know what people are expecting
Horrible, does not know how to teach! Rambles on about things unrelated to course content and makes exams extremely difficult

Horrible. Her midterms and assignments are great, but her final and her answer key for it is insane! Crazy how you can go from being an A+ student to practically failing the final even though you prepared for it. It wasnt even a hard final, it was just the wonky marking and questionable answers she used. Avoid! No amount of preparation can help!

I dont understand the negative reviews! She is the nicest prof and funny! Her midterms are very easy and her final was harder than the midterms but I found it still relatively easy as long as you study! Everything you need can be found on her slides so you dont need the textbook to study and you get 24+ hrs to finish it! Would take her again!

Shes extremely understanding when you run into difficulties and always answers her emails within a business day. Her midterms and final are fair and involve everything she talks about in class. The final was heavier but if you study it will be fine. She has quizzes and extra projects to make up for if you didnt do well on a midterm.

35% final exam was brutal. In the form of a take home exam which she said would take 3 hours but took the entire day and questions were extremely difficult. The rest of the course was fine but the final was the worst thing ever!

The class is composed of 2 midterms, case studies, one evaluation and one final exam. She is extremely caring for 65% of the grades. However, the 35% final exam is a completely different story. She claimed that the final could be done in 3h which is something impossible. For people taking her class in future, just be aware of the final exam.

I really enjoyed her she was super nice and had so many options for grades with a cool sketch project Im glad to have chosen. Her exams are open 24+ hours and interesting applied knowledge/ case style which I really enjoy especially being online. Overall would take her again interesting course and taught well

2 midterms (15%,20%)-she asked very specific questions for which you need to understand details about the course material, case studies/video 13% (I did the former-they were fun but required some thinking), and quizzes & a final. Main concern: she was disrespectful, unorganized, and blatantly ignored my emails when I asked for help or clarification
LOVED Dr Beaulieu. Beginning of the semester the lectures took some adapting but my the end, the material was clearly presented, exams were challenging but was necessary to study.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Very boring professor. So many different softwares that made it very difficult to keep up. A majority of the classes were not taught by her, she used other videos. Exams were very difficult and seemed beyong a firsy year introduction class.

I took this class with Beaulieu in Winter 2019. I don't dislike a lot of professors, but I really didn't like her or this class. The midterms weren't bad, but the final was so difficult, and there was so much material to study. She gave participation marks which helped a bit. This is the lowest grade I've ever gotten in any class in my life.

This was a tough class. I doubt that some questions on the exams (midterm and final) is at a first year level, looks like its a 3rd level class question. Never trust the teacher when shes says it should take like 1h(midterm) or 3h (final) took my way more time for both. Open book is great but it doesnt compensate for the level of some questions

She's really nice and you can tell she cares about her students. She gives a lot of assignments which can help boost your grade. She's always accessible and tries to connect the theoretical material to real life situations. The exams are pretty difficult so make sure to take good notes during lectures.

This prof is really nice and has a good sense of humour. Most of my classes were in YouTube video format and the information is clearly given but be prepared to take A LOT of notes. Her PowerPoints are also available and I recommend trying to understand the concepts instead of just memorizing them.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: The exams were not equivalent to the class material. And before any TA or past student start talking I toke bio HL in hs which is equivalent to first year bio and it was easier than this bs. She said it was a 3 hrs exam then why did the class average to taking 10 hrs? 16 pages all mise en situation questions and only given 14hrs starting at 5am.��

This was the worst final exam that i have ever done, ever. It did not reflect the material at all and was insanely hard. i took 4 hours to do the exam and it still wasnt enough. if the course notes were supposed to help me, how come nothing was identical between the notes and the exam? on top of that this class had an insane workload
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Tell student that the final could be completed in 3h... it took me 11+ h and Im still not confident in my answer. The 14h window is nice but sometimes I still feel Im running out of time. She said google wasnt needed and we could find everything in our notes is questionable.

J'ai bien aimé le cours! Tous ses examens sont basés sur les objectifs d'apprentissage (sur chaque ppt elle met les objectifs reliés au chapitre. Elle publie aussi une fiche complète de ses objectifs). Ce que je vous suggère: Faire un document et répondre à chaque objectif au fil du semestre. C'est une excellente façon d'étudier.

She's very resourceful, transitioned to online well. Her in class lecturing leaves a lot to be desired. Very dry, boring, but the slides are all you need. Cram/study those and you'll be in a good position. Its memorization 101, but its a lot and it comes at you fast. Second part (2nd midterm material) is deceptively complicated.

I had her when uni went online, so prior to online she was not great, looked like she didn't enjoy the class and was very boring. He midterms are really easy. ONLY LEARN THE BASICS. She give a lot of detail but when the midterms comes down to it, they're super simple. When classes went online, she did a really good transition and it was easy.

Don't bother getting the textbook it was completely useless imo and personally I did not rely heavily on taking notes, rather I made practice Qs for myself based on her powerpoints which were pretty thorough (this helped me a lot for the second midterm) and practice drawing diagrams! Come to class for the participation Brightspace quizzes

I appreciated SmartBio, I find it rare that you get useful homework in a class. The exams were very heavy, but they reflected the course material well. Make sure that you understand the diagrams super well, a lot of people (me lol) messed up on the first exam because of that.

Her lectures are not super engaging, however, her grading criteria is very clear. I relied on that and was able to get through the course so I strongly recommend doing that. Also, she provides opportunities for many bonus participation marks which were a saving grace.

She's kinda boring but she explains the materiel really well so if u go to class, take good notes and maybe with the help of the manuel, you should do pretty good. I got an 82% on my first midterm and the class average was a 64% so trust me. Also, those smartbio videos will save your life, that's basically all I studied for my second midterm

midterms were so so easy and if youre in a good group the case studies were very easy too, but the exam was much more challenging and lowered my grade significantly, relatively course overall tho just be ready for the final

Full disclosure, microbio was a super tough course for me. Dr. Beaulieu was always very nice and helpful in her office hours, but her teaching style never really benefitted my learning. Prepare to cram a ton of material into your head only to be asked about some very minuscule details. Group projects were a nice mark booster though

Yeah this prof was mediocre but not terrible. Really did not appreciate the million slides to study from post-midterm 2, plus the final was tougher than midterms. I will say she does give bonus and makes up for some questions she feels were not worded properly, so she's not arrogant about her mistakes which I can't say about some profs at this uni.
Her midterms weren't bad; they were pretty easy actually. But her final was absolutely brutal and tested on some content that was either never taught, or from the corner of her 10000000 slides.

She includes any additional information you need in the text section of her slides so if you miss a class someday you won't fall super far behind, lots of group assignments to boost your mark and the tests are fair. Use the learning goals for midterms and exams and you will do great in her class! Would recommend for a GPA boost to science students!
Such a sweet lady, she wants you to succeed, and is passionate about her field. Put the work in, study everything, and you'll do just fine.

i Agree with the last post. Take in English as the bio teachers have better reviews. The material isnt hard it how this person teaches. I will not take any further classes for her after doing this one for her. Read reddit cause its all previous students. If enough students dont schedule this class the Uni will have to review it

I will be honest, if you are a first year and looking for a class that will have a teacher who actually cares about the studentswould opt this class in English instead. Such a huge difference between chapeau and her. I did well in the class so not unhappy but that final was poorly written. And impossible.

She is a decent teacher but makes the material seem boring because she reads off the slides (almost fell asleep a few times). Even so, I recommend attending the class, because she has graded activities that can help bring your grade up slightly.
She really does the best she can, but the class is dry. Listening through the lectures is painful. Her tests are also pretty tough.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: As a person, she is sweet. She tries her best to teach well although she does tend to read off her slides. Yes, there is a lot of material to cover. I found her tests hard but she doesn't try to trick you. She is accessible outside class and very friendly when you ask her a question. Trust me, she's decent as a prof, just tough for her exams.
La matière du cour est bon mais elle est le problème.
Very good prof! Shes too smart to be teaching this class. Lots of chances to earn marks.
Its not easy but shes a very good prof. Go in with an open mind; its just a very dry class and I think it requires memory. Overall shes a very good person and tries hard.

Elaine is by far the worst prof I've had. She stands at the front of the class and reads off her slides. She doesn't even know what's going on in her own class. I could get up there and teach better than her.

I actually quite liked her. People just give her a hard time because the material isn't as simple as previous biology courses, although she explains it very well, is definitely very understanding and cares about her students. She's very passionate about her work and if you put in the necessary effort, you'll do fine.

I cry everyday and don't even know if ill make it looool but hey, study hard, read a lot, stay positive and we can get through this together (her exams are super detailed so learn little details and do EVERY participation point u can)! Nothings impossible, work for it. summers around the corner.

Its a very boring class but she is a really kind professor. I think she is teaching a very hard subject where you need to just memorize everything, but honestly she is a decent prof, work hard, and you will be more than fine.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Test heavy', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Worst microbio course ever - spends more time talking and explaining material that is not relevant to what she will test us on. She is aware that she does that and is frank about that - yet she doesn't match her exam questions to what she teaches. Insanely heavy course load - if she's you're only option take the course with easy af electives
Tough Grader, and doesn't explain well.
She is an awful prof. She expects us to know everything before she even teaches it. When students ask her questions during the lecture, i find that her answers to can be very rude and unexpected.
Makes the subject interesting. Personally thought it was a great class. I would definitely take this prof again. Easy exams if you study properly. Very possible to get an A in her class.

Professor Beaulieu is really passionate about microbiology, and that comes through in her lectures! But the lectures are a bit hard to follow, so sometimes the textbook really helps. She posts learning objectives that are very helpful for midterm/exam studying. Overall a good prof, just make sure you study!

Good prof overall. Sometimes lectures can veer off into material that's not entirely relevant to the midterms or exams, but it's not much of an issue considering that 99% of the testable learning objectives can be answered from the slides. Allocate time for group assignments a few days in advance, since they are somewhat time-consuming.

The class is very organized and has lots of opportunities for marks (15% midterms, homework and mastering assignments). She gave us Learning Objectives before both midterms and the final which strictly outlines what to study. Overall good class but lots to study.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: The course material is good but the way she writes her tests is awful, she focuses on images in the corner of the slides rather than the big global concepts like DNA transcription! The smart biology program is a very good tool! Her bonus points with echo360 and her online quizzes are generous but the final was nearly 30 pages of irrelevant material

Lectures are boring but you need to pay attention to get necessary info. Gives a lot of reading that I didn't find important for comprehension. Exams are super detail oriented. The first part of her class is much easier than the second. Study hard and take little points where you can get them (ex : biolingo, echo360, smartbiology)
great teacher, kinda tough though. read the textbook, study the stuff.
She's not very good at explaining the subject she's teaching and expects very specific answers in the tests/exam. she really just reads her slides which is just a waste of everyone's time and money.

Okay. People are way to intense on hating on this prof. Is she the best no. Would I want to take her class again no. But she isn't a bad prof. The way I see it is she puts a lot of effort into this class and expects you to do the same. 10% participation. 25% labs. Midterms are fine. Final is annoying. Its not an easy class but its 100% doable.
all i could say is : good luck
Don't think I've ever met a single person who took cell bio in french who actually liked her.
Her slides were more useful than her lectures. She would ramble on and on and it never really did make much sense.

If you took grade 12 biology and did well, chances are you'll do well in this class. Read the textbook, prepare for class and you'll get an A. It's straightforward, and she's straightforward too. This is an easy class and everything on the exam is not a surprise, since she gives you a study guide weeks before the exam. No reason to do poorly.

Yes there is a lot to memorize but if you go at every class and listen to her you can easily have an A. She is a though grader but if you listen carefully and study her notes there is no surprise in her exams. I read the comments before taking her class and I was really scared, don't be. Be a good student and you will do good.

She has lots of chances for you to get 100% on the participation aspects of the course (participation on echo360, smartbio participation), however her midterms and final are killer. You need to memorize exact details, not the big ideas from the lectures. Not a great prof.
Pas besoin d'être un biologiste pour avoir un A+, 10% de bonus et les examens sont vrmt facile, le cours à changer avec l'ajout de smartbio et biolingo donc n'ayez pas peur de prendre se cours....

Worst prof I have ever had. She has such surreal expectations and expects you to regurgitate all the information on her slides. If you don't read her textbook you won't understand her slides. She rushes through the lecture and will leave halfway through the revision periods. Grading scheme is rough. Don't take this class if you don't have to.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: She spends a lot of time reiterating the same concepts at the beginning of class and then has to rush through the last 75% of the lecture because she wasted so much time at the beginning repeating herself. Uses a lot of nonsense activities that don't really have a clear connection with the course. Grading scheme is super unfair. RIP

She's a horrible teacher. She gives us a lot of studying guides which is kind of good but her exams are way to difficult and complicated. If this class is mandatory for your program, just hang in there and study a lot. :)

This is one of the worst profs I have ever had. She seems to be under the impression that you should already know everything before she teaches it. She expects way too much from her students and she isn't helpful at all. She will not cover everything that is on the exam in class. This was a very frustrating class. Be prepared to study like crazy.

Worst professor I've ever had. Drop this class, don't even bother taking it with her. She gives lectures expecting you to already know everything so she doesn't explain anything. Her slides are useless. Her expectations are too hard even for Einstein. She won't help you if you email her about anything, super frustrating being an immersion student.
I would give her a zero if I could. Nightmare. Do not take this class if it is not mandatory.

One lecture 1h30min per week. No final. Lots of work but good grader. Instructions are not clear. Lectures don't reflect the homework. Lectures have too much material to cover not well explained. She wants to make us think and helps us learn to analyse data. You can tell she is passionate about the subject and cares about us and our feedback.

Elaine Beaulieu was by far the worst prof I have ever had. She didn't portray the subject matter efficiently, and honestly I walked out of her classes more confused than when I walked in. Both midterms and the final were fair, however the grading was ridiculous. You have to be a mind reader in order to know what exact vocab they want to see. AVOID.

Elle adore la matière qu'elle en enseigne mais n'est pas du tout capable de la de l de l'expliquer de manière comprehensive. Elle fait plein d'erreur d'orthographe mais s'attent a ce que tu n'en fasse aucune à l'examen. Le livre est  suggerer car il est beaucoup plus simple qu'elle. Elle est toujours très vague dans ses réponses et ses examens.

Pros: She answers all emails with detail and in person, no matter how good/bad your french is. (I'm in immersion) She seems to be passionate which helps in lectures.  Cons: Her marking schemes are "it's either right or wrong" even with very subjective questions. This is what ruined me. You have to know exactly what she wants as answers.

Her powerpoints are horribly unorganized, even she seems lost in her own content. Answers questions vaguely, and keeps insisting that it's because we're hardly scratching the surface, that she can't really be any clearer... The textbook is a life saver, you'll drown without it. Exams aren't too bad though, as long as you're prepared.

Je n'ai vraiment pas aimé ce professeure. Même en dehors des cours, elle réponds de façon très floue aux questions concernant la matière ou les examens. Elle est parfois confuse dans ses propres explications ce qui est encore plus mélangeant. À ne pas prendre si ce n'est pas un cours obligatoire!!!

Man, just open  your textbook and read. Ur gonna go to class and leave empty-handed if you don't read beforehand. Also, be very clear in your answers on midterms, as in don't write "many" write "more than one". Her tests aren't hard as in you could have the right answer but didn't express it specifically how it's written in the book. So practice!
Hype 80s dance videos. Junior high teacher vibe.
She plays weird videos in the middle of her lectures and it's pretty annoying and throws off your concentration.

ELLE COMPRENDS ET AIME CE QU'ELLE FAIT MAIS N'ARRIVE PAS A LE COMMUNIQUER DU COUP SI TU NE LIS PAS LE LIVRE,TU PERDS LE CONTROLE ET SES DIAPOS NE SERVENT A RIEN ELLE N EST PAS CLAIRE DANS SES EXPLICATIONS ET ELLE TE COMPLIQUE LA VIE CE COURS EST PAS A NEGLIGER SINON A LA FIN CA SERA UN E OU D FOR SURE! CES EXAMS SONT TRES DIFFICILE ET TRES LONG

The other comment wasn't kidding about strict memorization (don't take it if you're not good at memorizing names of metabolites, enzymes, pathways, etc.; there's A LOT of them and it's a cumulative exam). The content was kind of dry, midterm was strict on mark distribution (say goodbye to passing with part marks cause there ain't none given!)
Her notes are all over the place and unorganized. Hated the fact that you had to read the textbook to understand her notes. I do not recommend this class.

Very boring professor and sometimes speaks too slowly. Her slides are packed so no need to take notes (trust me, I've tried). Make sure to READ the book, it will help. She'll sometimes go off on a long explanation for 30 minutes, then will say "this won't be on the test" and she's often right. To succeed, study groups are a big help!

If I hadn't needed this class I never would have taken it. She gives readings to do in the book and make sure you read them and study them, because she will ask questions from stuff she never mentioned in class. I found I had to dedicate more time to this class then my others, which sucked. Also don't be afraid to get a tutor,it's worth it.

She pretends to know everything in biology and she is very condescending. Her grading is very tough, and it seems like if she doesn't understand  a topic she will assume the student has no knowledge about it either. I am glad I won't have to deal with her anymore! Worst prof in Bio

She uploads recordings of her lectures so they're really helpful if you didn't understand something in class. She isn't too clear on what is on the exam and what is not (although she does try to explain!). Her slides are packed with text. The exam is fair but she expects you to make extravagant connections to drug tests and research in real life...

Her slides are not organized and her lectures put you to sleep. Just listen to the recordings at 1.5x speed and read the book and you will do amazing. Exam questions are very precise so memorize the material very well (also try to understand for the developpment questions).

Her tests were really easy and the lectures were so short. Sometimes we had just a 45 minute lecture instead of 1h30min. She speaks really slowly and her voice put me to sleep sometimes. Her ideas are very unclear and jumbled up, she's constantly saying "this won't be on the test" so you don't even know what to study anymore. She was mediocre

She cares for her student and knows her stuff but has trouble explaining it. Her power points are very unclear, I bought the SOS review packages which helped me ALOT. Her exams reflect the material but she's very specific when it comes to the answer she's looking for which makes it hard to get a good grade in the development part of the exam.

Pretty good prof: pretty good at explaining and pretty interesting. Gives a lot of examples (which is confusing because she says you don't need to know all of the examples by heart, but you do need to know some of them). The mid-term seemed easy, but the grading was tough. Of course, there is a lot of memorisation, so pay attention in class.

Good prof overall. She doesn't expect you to memorize every little detail and her exam was fairly easy if you studied enough. Her powerpoints have not enough information sometimes, but read the manuel and you'll be fine.

Okay it's true her powerpoints are empty but she's a GREAT professor. Unlike most bio profs she doesn't want you to memorize EVERYTHING, she wants you to understand certain concepts that's it. Her midterms are easy. Powerpoints are basically empty because she doesn't want you to memorize useless things that won't help you in life! She's great!

VERY unclear, dont get me wrong she knows her stuff. However, when it comes to teaching it... Little bit of a stumble. My tip to you is to buy the exam aids by SOS ottawa. These study aids will be offered to you by an SOS representative before class or by email... BUY IT!!! helps a lot !!!!!
slides make no sense and dont follow a clear order.

The material in this course is strictly memorization. If you want to do well, just memorize the slides that she gives you. Her lecturing is rather dry as she only reads off of the slides. The true/false sections on the midterms and final try and trick you but the multiple choice and fill in the blanks are fairly straight forward.
